{
  "stem": "9701.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were apparently people in those camps who were artists or writers or had different professions.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And without any books or without any tools, they gave lectures.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, my mother attended lectures on literature.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were people that had-- could sing, and she attended, quote, unquote, 'concerts.' My father took courses in electrical engineering, in photography without any tools, without cameras, without anything.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was all in-- wanting to keep their minds alert and to keep their minds off the-- probably the difficult life that they were leading and to prepare them for, you know, another profession maybe, that maybe my father could become a photographer or an electrician or something like that.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think that is a form of resistance, because you could-- I'm sure there were people who just sat in a corner and vegetated.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the-- in July of 1942, my mother was sent from Camp de Gurs to Camp de Rivesaltes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's C-A-M-P, new word, D-E, new word, capital R-I-V-E-S-A-L-T-E-S, which was sort of halfway between Gurs and Les Milles.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the amazing thing is a letter that she wrote to me after she arrived in Rivesaltes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she-- and to me, it was like a travel log.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I thought, wow, she's taking a wonderful trip.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I wish I could have been on that trip.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She talks about getting a glimpse of the grotto in Lourdes and said-- told me how indescribably beautiful it is, and that she was coming-- the train that she was on was coming past fields of weaving corn or wheat and so on, that she saw tropical fruits on the trees, oranges and bananas, got a glimpse of the blue Mediterranean.",
      "word_count": 61
    }
  ],
